    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Jesse McKinley's article was a nice look at the opportunities online for keeping abreast of theater news. However, I can think of one major site he missed: www.broadwaybeat .com, the Internet companion to the wonderful television magazine series ''Broadway Beat.'' What makes the site remarkable is that it lets the stars do the talking, so the information is often firsthand.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Jesse McKinley's article was a nice look at the opportunities online for keeping abreast of theater news. However, I can think of one major site he missed: www.broadwaybeat .com, the Internet companion to the wonderful television magazine series ''Broadway Beat.'' What makes the site remarkable is that it lets the stars do the talking, so the information is often firsthand.</p>
        <p>Since Mr. McKinley didn't mention it, I will: a search engine is a Web browser's best friend.</p>
        <p>KEVIN DAWSON  Sunland, Calif.</p>
        <p>THEATER ON THE WEB</p>
      </block>
